reviews.text: We ordered catering from Resto the day of an event because our previous caterer dropped out unexpectedly. Resto was amazing in helping us create a unique menu for our needs and delivering it perfectly on time. Our guests really enjoyed the food which was hot and fresh. Pizzas, pasta, burgers and salads - everything was great and the staff was so helpful

The portions here are very generous, but then you taste the food.  It's 3xcellent with a varied menu of steak, ribs, pizza, fajitas, pizza, pasta and burgers for example. Would fit in Australia/UK as an Italian no problem.  Good sized servings of tasty pizza, pasta and a lot of other things.  Pasta cooked properly (not overcooked like so many local restaurants).  Excellent Greek salad with real feta.  It's not "upmarket", but it's a good family style Italian with tasty food at reasonable prices.  Main downside is that it's not large and often overrun with children!

result.name: Hong Kong Gold Coast Piazza

reviews.text: I love come to Gold Coast Piazza once a while to enjoy delicious dim sum at the restaurant. Convenient to come by public transport from Tuen Mun. This is a nice place to walk around and enjoy a relaxing weekend with friends and family. Parking space available but filled up really quickly during the weekend. Would recommend to make reservation if you are dining in one of the restaurants here.

The main character of the Gold Coast is the Paza where shops and restaurants are including McDonald. It’s a wonderful place to unwind or cool down after sun at the Golden beach nearby. Not only the place is adorned with beautiful garden but also lovely architectural buildings. This is again a nice and wonderful place to visit and photo taking during weekdays. The weekend is out of question packed with visitors and sometimes stalls selling food and handicrafts.
This is the plaza next to Gold Coast Hotel. This is the best place to go if you're in this part of Hong Kong
Excellent grocery store and lots of places to eat.  Decent view of the yachts towards the back, makes for great views during sunsets.

Mediocre food in a great waterside setting.  Sit on waterfront side possible.
Nice grocery store here.

reviews.text: Nice hotel outside of the city with a slightly different feel to the rest of Hong Kong. They offer themed rooms which is great for a kids bday celebration. Nice playroom but only offer 1 hour free session per day. Buffet is good but can get very busy so book early during peak periods. Pool is nice with outdoor water play area. The hotel grounds and gardens are well kept and nice to walk around!

The place is excellent. The only problem is getting a room at a good price. You have to shop when they have a sale. Try to book a room when they're having a sale. I guess it depends on what time of year you're going to be there. But you'll have a good time at this hotel. There's a nice Shopping Plaza near the hotel about a 8 minute walk. They have McDonald's and a bunch of other restaurants and a 7-Eleven at the plaza. Also the bus stop is not too far away. And I have taxis waiting in the lobby if you need that. But I prefer bus and Subway to get around Hong Kong.

Pretty quiet during weekdays. Good for a short get away. Decent rooms with good view. Right next to a nice beach. Can take bus here. If you insist on driving, there is a big public metered parking lot just in front of hotel entrance if you don't want to use the hotel's expensive valet service.

We booked a top floor room with sea view and got a room on the middle floor with a view of mostly the car park. We could see a tiny part of the beach that had heaps of workers and tractors still renovating and it was a zone we could not enter. The walk along the whole beach was renovating areas. We also had a buffet lunch that was expensive and had listened to very loud jack hammers while eating because of renovations to the building. It would have been nice of them to discount us due to unpleasant renovations or at least tell us about it when booking our room. And the booking of the rooms is all a lie and total rip off for a sea view booking. The staff are not friendly compared to other places we stayed in Hong Kong.
Great Hotel. Great location. Sparkling clean. Great hospitality. Extremely well connected to city.
